body:
Can we reference a Jira here please (an existing or a new one). Also I don't understand why we need this renaming in cayenne-server/src/main/java/org/apache/cayenne/map/Relationship.java:

```
@@ -91,12 +91,11 @@ public void setSourceEntity(Entity sourceEntity) {
/**
* Sets relationship target entity. Internally calls <code>setTargetEntityName</code>.
*/
- public void setTargetEntity(Entity targetEntity) {
+ public void setTargetEntityName(Entity targetEntity) {
if (targetEntity != null) {
setTargetEntityName(targetEntity.getName());
- }
- else {
- setTargetEntityName(null);
+ } else {
+ setTargetEntityName((String) null);
}
}
```

https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAY-1984
cdbimport doesn't flatten many to many relationships

about 
- public void setTargetEntity(Entity targetEntity) {
- public void setTargetEntityName(Entity targetEntity) {

I've been really misleaded by name of method. It sets string with target entity's name and called as setTargetEntity. Everywhere where I see call setTargetEntity I believe that TargetEntity by it self is necessary information and link/reference to this entity will be stored in relationship, but it is not truth. Everything that this method doing is null checking and entity name extraction. Therefore it must be named according with expected result, in order to avoid miscomprehension of further usage of it and  reading code with it's calls.
